body:
I don&#039;t know how to put evidence of this without name sharing so I will just explain it to you and you guys let me know if it&#039;s my fault or not. I just want to understand if I was in the wrong? 

            I was in a game with a support. We went in and in the end got first blood. I died in the progress and my support kept attacking their ADC with auto- attacks. I went back to rewatch this part of the story to get my facts straight. I pinged him to back 5 times in total and then he ignores each ping and goes in on them. He dies and I type &quot;...&quot; to which he replies &quot; stop pinging me it&#039;s distracting&quot; and I said, &quot;then back.&quot; 
           This is when all hell breaks loose and he runs down mid and kills himself claiming he was gonna take mid turret down one hit at a time. I tell the enemy team to report, and they laugh at me. Fine with that because I know my team understands me. Little did I know, they would soon turn against me as well claiming I started this whole thing and that it was my fault for being toxic. Pretty sure everyone then reported me after the game and this support came out looking like Batman; fighting against the ever growing injustice of toxicity.
